ZCZC GE70
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 082300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING THE AZORES HIGH EXTENDS NEWARDS ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES
AS A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IN THE NORWEGIAN SEA MOVS NWARDS AND SLWY
FILLS. LATER ON TUESDAY A DEEP ATLANTIC LOW WILL MOV W OF ICELAND WITH PRESSURE
REMAINING HIGH TO THE SE. DURING WEDNESDAY THE DEEP LOW NEAR ICELAND WILL
SLWY FILL AS HIGH PRESSURE DOMINATES TO THE S AND E. OVERNIGHT WEDNESDAY
INTO THURSDAY A WEAK LOW WILL MOV NEWARDS ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES AS A FURTHER
DEEP LOW DEVELOPS JUST W OF ROCKALL. THIS REACHING BAILEY LATER THURSDAY.
ON MONDAY EVENING GALES WILL AFFECT CULLERCOATS SEA AREAS N OF 58 DEGREES
N. OVERNIGHT THESE GALES WILL SLWY EASE NWARDS WITH NO HAZARDOUS WINDS IN
CULLERCOATS BY DAWN TUESDAY. OVERNIGHT TUESDAY INTO WEDNESDAY GALES WILL
DEVELOP IN THE W OF FAIR ISLE THESE EASING DURING THE MORNING. NO FURTHER
HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP UNTIL GALES REACH FAIR ISLE LATE ON THURSDAY
